<h2>Overview</h2><p>If you're looking to spruce up the rear seat of your 2015 Jeep Wrangler JK Unlimited and add some extra functionality, installing Bartact seat covers is a great choice. Not only do they provide impressive protection against wear and tear, but they also feature MOLLE/PALS webbing, allowing you to add compatible gear easily. This tutorial guides you through the installation process, detailing everything you need to transform your rear seats.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This article will discuss the installation of Bartact rear seat covers specifically for the JK Unlimited. We’ll guide you through unboxing the product, the necessary steps for installation, and tips for attaching MOLLE bags. By the end, you'll have a solid understanding of how to enhance your Jeep's interior.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Unboxing the Covers:</strong> Upon opening the package, you’ll find two headrest covers along with bottom and back panels for both sides of the split bench seat. The covers are designed to fit snugly and are compatible with MOLLE gear.</li><li><strong>Preparing for Installation:</strong> Before installing, familiarize yourself with the Velcro attachments and the 550 cord provided. The cord can be used to further secure the covers if desired.</li><li><strong>Installing the Driverside Seat Cover:</strong> Start with the driver's side. Flip the seat cover inside-out for easier application. Slip it over the seat, ensuring the Velcro aligns correctly, before folding it over and securing it in place.</li><li><strong>Attaching Seat Backs:</strong> You’ll have to remove the headrests by pushing a button on either side of their posts. Once removed, slip the cover on and use the provided Velcro to secure it at the bottom.</li><li><strong>Installing the Passengerside Seat Cover:</strong> The process is similar. You might need to undo the seatbelt for better access. Follow the alignment of seams and velcro it down after ensuring all parts fit snugly.</li><li><strong>Final Touches:</strong> After securing both covers, adjust the headrests back in place. You can use the MOLLE webbing for additional storage options.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>When removing headrests, feel for the push buttons to ensure you don't damage the mechanism.</li><li>For tighter fitting, use the 550 cord provided to secure the covers further.</li><li>Take your time to align the seams properly during installation to achieve a clean and professional look.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing Bartact rear seat covers on your JK Unlimited can enhance both the aesthetics and functionality of your vehicle. By following this step-by-step guide, you can ensure a smooth and efficient installation process. Enjoy the added protection and versatility these covers offer, ideal for any Jeep enthusiast looking to make the most of their off-road adventures.</p>

